# RetroTracker server configuration.
# Loaded via Node's built-in `--env-file=.env` flag (Node 20.6+).
# Add the flag to your dev script or prod CMD; this file is gitignored.

# ---------- Backend ----------
# In dev (`npm run dev`) the backend is always on. In prod this gates
# whether `/api/*` is mounted at all. Default: off.
# RETROTRACKER_BACKEND=1

# Where projects/samples/modules are stored on disk.
# Defaults: ./data in dev, / in the container.
# RETROTRACKER_DATA_DIR=/var/lib/retrotracker

# ---------- OIDC auth (optional) ----------
# All five OIDC_* vars are required together. Partial config throws at
# boot. Unset them all to run anonymously (single shared bucket, no
# user accounts — see CLAUDE.md "Optional OIDC auth").
#
# Recommended provider: Logto Cloud (free tier). Set up a "Traditional
# web" application; the issuer URL takes the form
# https://<tenant>.logto.app/oidc.

# OIDC_ISSUER=https://your-tenant.logto.app/oidc
# OIDC_CLIENT_ID=
# OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET=
# OIDC_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:5173/api/auth/callback

# Cookie-signing secret. Must decode to >= 32 bytes (UTF-8 or base64).
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 48
# OIDC_COOKIE_SECRET=

# Where Logto sends the browser after RP-initiated logout. Defaults to "/".
# OIDC_POST_LOGOUT_REDIRECT=/

# ---------- Misc ----------
# Override the version string baked into the build. Normally derived
# from git tags via scripts/version.sh, but useful in containers where
# `.git` isn't available.
# APP_VERSION=v0.0.0-dev

# Port the prod Node server binds to. Default: 80.
# PORT=8080
